      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For high-level executives, a polished appearance signals competence and respect for the gravity of their position. This generally means impeccable tailoring in conservative, dark colors—think charcoal or navy suits—paired with high-quality, subtle accessories. Grooming should be meticulous; hair should be neatly styled, and facial hair, if present, must be perfectly maintained. The goal is to look authoritative, not flashy, which is best achieved through understated quality.",
